text: Anthony Magnacca is an Australian retired soccer player who last played for Box Hill United in his home country. He has played in the Norwegian Premier League, his first professional stint, in 2001. ==Career== On trial with SK Brann of the Norwegian Premier League in 2001,Australier til Brann Vg.no Magnacca saw Brann as a springboard to a higher league upon transferring to the club and was received well, earning a salary of about 30000 krone per month.Et vindu til Europa Ba.no He then made his league debut opposing Bodo- Glimt, in which Brann lost 5–1, after being praised by the coach for his assiduous efforts in a friendly.Australier klar for Brann-debut Vg.no The Australian's debut would be his only appearance in his loan to Norway which lasted just two months. == References == == External links == * Magnacca at WorldFootball * MA Profiles at OzFootball Category:Australian people of Italian descent Category:Australian expatriate soccer players Category:1978 births Category:SK Brann players Category:Australian expatriates in Norway Category:Canberra Cosmos players Category:Heidelberg United FC players Category:FC Bulleen Lions players Category:Australian soccer players Category:Association football midfielders Category:Living people Category:Expatriate footballers in Norway Category:Newcastle Jets FC players Category:Preston Lions FC players Category:Hume City FC players Category:South Melbourne FC players Category:Green Gully SC players Category:Sunshine George Cross FC players Category:Eliteserien players
